{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB1213", "title": "Restitution: priority.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Restitution", "priority"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "The California Constitution entitles the victim of a crime to restitution. Existing law requires the court in each criminal case to order a convicted defendant to pay full restitution to the victim and a separate restitution fine, as specified. Existing law makes a restitution order in a case in which a victim suffered economic loss as a result of the defendant's conduct, as specified, enforceable as if it were a civil judgment.\n\nThis bill, the Restitution First Act, would also require that a restitution order be paid before all fines, restitution fines, penalty assessments, and other fees, as specified. The bill would also make nonsubstantive, conforming changes."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Introduced. To print.", "date": "2025-02-21", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["introduction"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 24.", "date": "2025-02-22", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Read first time.", "date": "2025-02-24", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Com. on PUB. S.", "date": "2025-03-10", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": [{"name": "Com. on PUB. S.", "entity_type": "organization", "organization_id": null}]}, {"description": "In committee: Set, first hearing. Hearing canceled at the request of author.", "date": "2025-03-19", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classi